R for Biology Data Science Workshop Series

Faculty of Natural and Agricultural Sciences, University of Pretoria

Joey Hulbert

April 23 - May 30, 2019

Welcome!

The purpose of this page is to provide resources for the R for Biology Data Science Workshop Series for postgrad students and postdocs in the Faculty of Natural and Agricultural Sciences at the University of Pretoria in South Africa.

  • Workshop Series
    • April 23, 2019. (Please note this session only starts at 4pm)
      • Session 1 - Introduction to RStudio.
        • Learn the basics of coding, importing data, installing packages, and managing projects.
    • April 30, 2019.
      • Session 2 - Introduction to data visualization with ggplot2 Part 1.
        • Create plots (histograms, boxplots, barplots), faceting, adjustments, etc.
    • May 7, 2019.
      • Session 3 - Introduction to data visualization with ggplot2 Part 2.
        • Customizing plot aesthetics (colors, labels, italics, etc.), saving and exporting.
    • May 14, 2019.
      • No session offered
    • May 21, 2019.
      • Session 4 - Introduction to data transformation with dplyr Part 1.
        • Filter data, summarize data (e.g. easily calculate means for groups), add variables.
    • May 28, 2019.
      • Session 5 - Introduction to data transformation with dplyr Part 2.
        • Merge datasets, combine tables, introduction to stringr, introduction to R markdown.

Location

All sessions will be offered in the auditorium of the Forestry and Agricultural Biotechnology Institute (FABI).

Directions

The audiotorium is on the bottom floor of the FABI 2 building, but you will need to enter from the FABI 1 building. Head left from the front door and continue to the left (two additional left turns) until you reach the auditorium from the front door.
